article.headline: S. Dakota St. 64, W. Illinois 55
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. -- Dale Moss scored 13 points and Kai Williams had a double-double as South Dakota State beat Western Illinois 64-55 on Thursday, handing the Leathernecks their first Summit League loss. Williams had 10 points and 10 rebounds for the Jackrabbits (2-3, 7-10), who had five players in double figures. Anthony Cordova and Clint Sargent had 12 points apiece and Garrett Callahan added 10. Williams' 3-pointer with 45 seconds left gave the Jackrabbits a 25-24 lead at the break. SDSU shot 53 percent and went 15-for-18 from the free throw line. Western Illinois (3-1, 6-9) was led by David Dubois with 21 points and seven rebounds. Josh Rivers had three 3-pointers and 15 points.
